               <head>Histories of Qutbshahi state</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85110171 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008114810">
                  <summary>Collection of official regnal chronicles relating to the reign of Abū al-Muẓaffar Sulṭān Muḥammad Quṭb Shāh, and the foundations of the Quṭbshāhī/Quṭbkhānī State at Ḥaydar'ābād and Gulkundah (Golconda); formerly belonging to the Elliot library; letter (dated Wullurr, July 1853) attached to 1st flyleaf describes this copy as affiliated to an original belonging to the Qutbshahi royal family; collated and checked agaist the original by Mirzā Muḥammad Ṭāhir (f. 576v)</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh95003049" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3676-item1">
                     <locus from="3r" to="352v">ff. 3r-352v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Anonymously written official chronicle on the foundation of the Quṭbshāhī/Quṭbkhānī Dynasty, based at Golkonda, possibly written for Abū al-Muẓaffar Sulṭān Muḥammad Quṭb Shāh</p>
                        <p>Machine-made multicoloured papers, blind stamped: S. Baurie Fils, Bordeaux</p>
                        <p>Dated (ff. 352v-353r): completed at the request of Mistar Vātar Īliyat Ṣāḥib Iskvayar Bahādur (Mr Walter Elliot, Esq.), Governor of the Southern Presidency, Madras, by Mīr Pādshāh, at Machhlī Bandar (Machilipatnam/Masulipatnam), Wednesday, ghurrah (=1st) Z̲ī Qaʿdah 1268/18 August 1852</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_6803">Tārīkh-i Sulṭān Muḥammad Quṭbshāhī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_6803">تأريخ سلطان محمّد قطبشاهى</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh95003049" n="2" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3676-item2">
                     <locus from="353r" to="576v">ff. 353r-576v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_14539748">Niẓām al-Dīn Aḥmad ibn ʿAbd Allāh al-Shīrāzī al-Ṣāʿidī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_14539748">نظام الدّين احمد ابن عبد الله الشّيرازى الصّاعدى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21816">Ḥadīqat al-salāṭīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21816">حدیقة السّلاطين</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Official regnal chronicle written for and covering the reign of the mid-seventeenth-century Quṭbshāhī/Quṭbkhānī ruler of the sultanate of Ḥaydar'ābād/Gulkundah, Abū al-Muẓaffar Sulṭān Muḥammad Quṭb Shāh</p>
                        <p>Account extends until the 16th regnal year, when it breaks abruptly before the colophon</p>
                        <p>Machine-made multicoloured papers, blind stamped: S. Baurie Fils, Bordeaux</p>
                        <p>Dated (f. 576v): completed at the request of Mistar Vātar Īliyat Ṣāḥib Iskvayar Bahādur (Mr Walter Elliot, Esq.), Governor of the Southern Presidency, Madras, by Mīr Pādshāh, at Machhlī Bandar (Machilipatnam/Masulipatnam), Monday, 2 Ṣafar 1269/15 November 1852</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
